<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | severancepayestimator.com"
  description="Privacy policy for severancepayestimator.com — how we handle data, including the case-review form, and use third-party services."
>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="byline">Last updated: July 2026</p>

  <p>
    This Privacy Policy describes how severancepayestimator.com ("we," "us," or "our"), operated by The Click Lab Agency LLC, handles information when you use our website. We are committed to being transparent about what we collect, how we use it, and who we share it with.
  </p>

  <h2>Information From Browsing the Calculator</h2>
  <p>
    Our calculator operates entirely in your browser. Any information you enter into the Severance Pay Estimator — including salary, years of service, industry, or state — is processed locally on your device and is never transmitted to our servers, stored in any database, or shared with third parties. We have no access to your calculation inputs or results.
  </p>

  <h2>The Case-Review Form and Attorney Sharing</h2>
  <p>
    The homepage also includes an optional Severance Negotiation case-review form. If you submit it, we collect your name, phone number, email address, a description of your case, and the time you gave consent. That information is shared with one or more attorneys or their agents licensed to practice in your jurisdiction, so they can evaluate your situation and contact you about it. The Click Lab Agency LLC is not a law firm, does not provide legal advice, and does not vet, endorse, or guarantee the attorneys in this network. Submitting the form does not create an attorney-client relationship with The Click Lab Agency LLC or with any attorney until and unless that attorney separately agrees to represent you. The Click Lab Agency LLC may be compensated for these referrals.
  </p>
  <p>
    By submitting the case-review form, you separately consent to be contacted by phone, text, and email — including by automated dialing technology — by The Click Lab Agency LLC and the attorneys or agents your information is shared with. That consent is not required to use any other part of the Site, and you can decline it simply by not submitting the form.
  </p>

  <h2>Automatically Collected Information</h2>
  <p>
    Like most websites, we use third-party services that may collect certain non-personally-identifiable technical information, including:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Browser type and version</li>
    <li>Operating system</li>
    <li>Pages visited and time spent on pages</li>
    <li>Referring URL</li>
    <li>Approximate geographic location (country/region, derived from IP address)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>This information is collected in aggregate and is used solely to understand how our site is used and to improve its content.</p>

  <h2>Google Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    We use Google Analytics to understand aggregate site traffic and user behavior. Google Analytics uses cookies and collects anonymized usage data. This data is processed by Google in accordance with their Privacy Policy at <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">policies.google.com/privacy</a>. You can opt out of Google Analytics tracking by installing the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Google AdSense</h2>
  <p>
    We display advertisements served by Google AdSense (publisher ID: pub-6434377544325972). Google uses cookies and similar technologies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this and other websites. You may opt out of personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Ads Settings</a>. For more information on how Google uses data from advertising partners, see <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Partner Sites policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    We do not set first-party tracking cookies. Third-party services (Google Analytics, Google AdSense) may set cookies in accordance with their own policies. You can control or delete cookies through your browser settings at any time.
  </p>

  <h2>Your Choices and Opting Out</h2>
  <p>
    The simplest opt-out is not to submit the case-review form. If you've already submitted it and want your information removed or want to withdraw consent to be contacted, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the subject line <strong>[OPT-OUT]</strong>, or visit <a href="https://theclicklab.agency/optout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">theclicklab.agency/optout</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>California Privacy Rights (CCPA/CPRA)</h2>
  <p>
    California residents have the right to know what personal information is collected, the right to delete personal information, and the right to opt out of the sale or sharing of personal information. Sharing your case-review submission with attorneys in exchange for compensation may be considered a "sale" or "sharing" of personal information under the CCPA/CPRA, and you can opt out through either channel above. Anonymous browsing of the calculator and guides alone is never sold or shared, because we don't collect anything from it. For questions about your California privacy rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>European Privacy Rights (GDPR)</h2>
  <p>
    If you are located in the EEA, UK, or Switzerland and choose to submit the case-review form, the legal basis for processing your information is your consent, which you may withdraw at any time using the opt-out channels above. Browsing the Site itself does not involve processing personal data about you.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    This site is not directed at children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13.
  </p>

  <h2>Links to Third-Party Sites</h2>
  <p>
    Our site may contain links to external websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those sites and encourage you to review their privacy policies.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The date at the top of this page reflects the most recent revision. Continued use of the site following any update constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For privacy-related questions, contact us at <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
